verbs.description: untrace (third-person singular simple present untraces, present participle untracing, simple past and past participle untraced)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove from the traces; to unharness.
(computing, programming, transitive) To remove a trace from.
examples: It is important to untrace a function before modifying its definition, since some tools may not be smart enough to realize that the version of reScale on the session frame is only for debugging!
